==English==
===Alternative spellings===
* [[shmuck]]
* [[shmuk]]

===Etymology===
From Yiddish [[שמאָק]] ''shmok'', literally ''[[penis]]'' (''vulgar''), from Old Polish [[smok]] (modern Polish: [[smok]], ''dragon)''.

===Noun===
'''schmuck'''
# ([[vulgar]]) the [[penis]]
# ([[vulgar]]) the [[foreskin]])
# ([[pejorative]]) an item or person that is considered [[useless]]
# ([[pejorative]]) a [[jerk]]; an [[unpleasant]] or [[detest]]able person

